VERSUS

Rajasthan Medical Services Corporation Ltd. (RMSCL),
Swasthya Bhawan, Tilak Marg, Jaipur – 302 015                            ...Respondent

APPLICATION UNDER SECTION 11(6) OF THE ARBITRATION AND CONCILIATION ACT, 1996
FOR APPOINTMENT OF SOLE ARBITRATOR

MOST RESPECTFULLY SHOWETH:

1. The Applicant is a construction company engaged in the business of civil construction.

2. The Respondent (RMSCL) issued Work Order No. RMSCL/2024-25/Works/4782 dated 05.05.2024
   for Construction of 300-Bed Hospital at Udaipur for a total contract value of ₹48,75,00,000.

3. Clause 25 of the CPWD GCC 2020 (applicable to the Contract) provides for resolution of disputes
   by a Sole Arbitrator to be appointed in accordance with the Arbitration & Conciliation Act, 1996.

4. Disputes have arisen between the parties regarding:
   a) Delay in site handover and compensation thereof (₹4.82 Crore)
   b) Withheld running bills (₹12.45 Crore)
   c) Variation Orders for extra work (₹6.15 Crore)
   d) Extension of Time for employer-caused delays
   e) Wrongful termination of contract on 15.01.2026

5. The Applicant issued a Legal Notice dated 12.12.2025 and a No Satisfaction Letter dated 15.01.2026.
   RMSCL has failed to appoint an arbitrator.

6. Total claim amount: ₹19.84 Crore + interest + arbitration costs.

PRAYER:
The Applicant most respectfully prays that this Hon'ble Court may be pleased to:
a) Appoint a Sole Arbitrator (preferably a retired District Judge or High Court Judge) to adjudicate
   the disputes between the parties.
b) Direct the parties to appear before the Arbitrator within 4 weeks.
c) Pass any other order as this Hon'ble Court deems fit.

Udaipur                                    Advocate for Applicant
Date: 10.02.2026
